[[Lieutenant general|Lt. Gen.]] '''Ahmed Awad Ibn Auf''' (born ~1954<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wikileaks.org/plusd/cables/08STATE61842_a.html|title=Cable: 08STATE61842_a|work=wikileaks.org|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>) ({{lang-ar|أحمد عوض بن عوف}}) is a [[Sudan]]ese [[General officer|general]] and [[politician]]. Auf is the current National [[Defense Minister]] of Sudan.<ref>https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/world-leaders-1/pdfs/SU.pdf</ref>
Auf previously served as Head of [[Military Intelligence]], and also Chairman of the [[Chief of staff|Joint Chiefs of Staff]] before he was relieved in June 2010 as part of a major military shakeup.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2010/06/11/uk-sudan-army-idUKTRE65A11Y20100611|title=Sudan retires general sanctioned over Darfur|work=Reuters UK|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref> Following his [[military]] service, he served as the Sudanese [[Ambassador]] to [[Oman]].
Auf was on a May 2007 list of individuals [[International sanctions|sanctioned]] by the [[United States]] due to his alleged role as a liaison between the [[Government of Sudan|Sudanese government]] and the [[Janjaweed]] in the [[Darfur War]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sudantribune.com/spip.php?article56160|title=Bashir appoints U.S. sanctioned general as new defence minister|work=sudantribune.com|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/sudan-appoints-new-defence-minister-531515314|title=Sudan appoints new defence minister|work=Middle East Eye|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref>
