=== By country ===
{{See also|List of countries by suicide rate}}

Suicide rates are highest in Europe's [[Baltic states]], where around 40 people per 100,000 die by suicide each year. The lowest rates are found mainly in Caribbean/West Indies nations and a few countries in Asia.<ref name="Staff 2002"/>

As many as 60,000 people commit suicide in [[Russia]] every year;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.rian.ru/russia/20061004/54514777.html|title=60,000 people commit suicide in Russia annually|first=|last=Sputnik|publisher=rian.ru|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref> approximately 30,000 people die by suicide each year in the [[United States]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/ncipc/factsheets/suifacts.htm|title=National Center for Injury Prevention and Control - Home Page-Injury Center-CDC|publisher=cdc.gov|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref> over 30,000 kill themselves in [[Japan]];<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://asia.news.yahoo.com/070607/kyodo/d8pjn43o0.html |title=Suicides in Japan top 30,000 for 9th straight year |publisher=Yahoo! |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070905215736/http://asia.news.yahoo.com/070607/kyodo/d8pjn43o0.html |archivedate=2007-09-05 |df= }}</ref> and about 25,000 commit suicide each year in [[China]].<ref>[http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/200110/30/eng20011030_83533.html 250,000 Chinese Kill Themselves Annually: Official]</ref> In western countries men commit suicide at four times the rate of women. Women are more likely to [[Parasuicide|attempt suicide]] than men.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nimh.nih.gov/health/publications/the-numbers-count-mental-disorders-in-america.shtml#WeissmanPrevalenceSui |title=The Numbers Count: Mental Disorders in America&nbsp;— Suicide |accessdate=2007-12-11 |publisher=National Institute of Mental Health |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071022033442/http://www.nimh.nih.gov/health/publications/the-numbers-count-mental-disorders-in-america.shtml#WeissmanPrevalenceSui |archivedate=2007-10-22 |df= }}</ref>

The countries of the former [[Soviet Bloc]] have the highest [[suicide rate]]  in the world. Rate of [[suicide in South Korea]] is the highest among any other East Asian countries. The region with the lowest suicide rate is [[Latin America]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/3639152.stm|title=BBC NEWS - In Depth - More killed by suicide than war|publisher=bc.co.uk|accessdate=19 March 2017}}</ref>

[[China]] is the only country in the world where the rate of suicide by women matches that of men, with statistics even showing a slightly higher number of female cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YqN-8XHDNX8C&pg=PA30|title=Why People Die by Suicide|first=Thomas|last=Joiner|date=30 September 2007|publisher=Harvard University Press|accessdate=19 March 2017|via=Google Books}}</ref>

