{{distinguish|Rufim Njeguš}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = | honorific-prefix = | name = Rufim Boljević | honorific-suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = Serbian | title = Metropolitan of Cetinje | image = | image_size = 250px | alt = | caption = | church = | archdiocese = | province = | metropolis = [[Metropolitanate of Cetinje]] | diocese = | see = [[Cetinje]] | elected = | appointed = | term = | term_start = 1662 or 1673 | quashed = | term_end = January 1685 | predecessor = [[Mardarije Kornečanin]] | opposed = | successor = [[Vasilije Veljekrajski]] | other_post = <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = | birth_date = Unknown | birth_place = Boljevići, [[Crmnica]] (modern [[Montenegro]]) | death_date = January 1685 | death_place = | buried = | nationality = | religion = [[Serbian Orthodox Church|Serbian Orthodox]] | residence = Cetinje | parents = | spouse = <!-- or | partner = --> | occupation = | profession = | previous_post = | education = | alma_mater = | motto = | signature = | signature_alt = | coat_of_arms = | coat_of_arms_alt = <!---------- Other ----------> | other = }}
'''Rufim Boljević''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Руфим Бољевић}}; {{floruit}} 1673 – d. January 1685) was the [[Serbian Orthodox]] [[Metropolitanate of Cetinje|Metropolitan (''vladika'') of Cetinje]] from 1662 or 1673 until his death in January 1685. He succeeded [[Mardarije Kornečanin]] ([[floruit|fl.]] 1640–59), and was succeeded by [[Vasilije Veljekrajski]].
==Life== Boljević was from [[Crmnica]], and belonged to the [[Plamenac]] brotherhood, and is scarcely mentioned as '''Rufim Plamenac''' (Руфим Пламенац).<ref name="PlamenacBojović1997">{{cite book|author1=Rade Turov Plamenac|author2=Jovan R. Bojović|title=Memoari|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VfwyAAAAMAAJ|year=1997|publisher=CID|page=515|quote=Руфим (Пламенац) Бољевић 1675}}</ref><ref name="JovićevićCvijović1995">{{cite book|author1=Ivo Jovićević|author2=Vladeta Cvijović|author3=Nikola Jovićević|title=O ljudima i događajima, 1892-1936: sjećanje jednog federaliste|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wPVNAAAAMAAJ|year=1995|publisher="Obod"|page=4|quote=А мислио је, можда, да на то има право будући је потоњи владика, од оних из разнијех племена, био његов предак Руфим Бољевић, дакле Руфим Пламенац. Да би у овом подухвату успио, пође он у Скадар код својих рођака ...}}</ref>
It is generally believed he succeeded [[Mardarije Kornečanin]], mentioned between 1640 and 1659.<ref name="Ivanović2006">{{cite book|author=Filip Ivanović|title=Problematika autokefalije Mitropolije Crnogorsko-primorske|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mP6OAAAAMAAJ|year=2006|publisher=Unireks|page=42|quote=Руфим Бољевић (помиње се 1673, 1675, 1682. и 1685.)}}</ref> The Cetinje see seems to have been unseated from 1660 until early 1662, when an unnamed Metropolitan of Cetinje is mentioned in a source from the [[Bay of Kotor]].<ref name=IZ>{{cite book|title=Историски записи|volume=9|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=K4oSAAAAIAAJ|year=1954|publisher=с.н.|pages=528–529|quote=Посли]е владике Мардари]а (1659), столица цетињског митрополита ни]е била, изгледа, попутьена током 1660 — 1. Почетком године 1662, у которским изворима помиње се владика цетињски. То ]е, бесумње, Рувим Бољевић. У ...}}</ref> Boljević is mentioned in sources from 1673, 1675, 1682 and 1685.<ref name="Ivanović2006"/> He funded the construction of [[Reservoir|water reservoir]] in [[Hilandar]] before being ortinated as Vladika.<ref>http://www.rastko.rs/rastko-cg/povijest/istorijat/istorijat_2_c.html</ref> It has been theorized that it was Boljević who was mentioned in 1662 (by I. Stjepčević and P. Kovijančić).<ref>{{cite book|title=Istorijski zapisi|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F4riAAAAMAAJ|year=1955|page=250|quote=... а ту би морало бити података да ]е и дал>е живио, ньегов наслз^зник, изгледа, ни]е био изабран до почетка 1662, а отада ]'е цеттьски митрополит Рувим Бол>евиК (И. СтдепчевиЬ я. Р. КовизаниЬ, Неколико података о Рувиму ...}}</ref> If he indeed had taken the seat in 1662, it means that he (as the Metropolitan) was one of two [[Arbitration|arbiters]] in the feud between ''harambaša'' Lazarić and Karučan from Crmnica, mentioned on November 2, 1662; as Boljević was from Crmnica, this has been taken as proof.<ref name=IZ/> It would also mean that he was active during the [[Cretan War (1645–69)]], in which many [[hajduks]] (brigands) from the region of Montenegro participated in, in the service of the [[Republic of Venice]]. A notable leader was [[Bajo Pivljanin]].
After the Cretan War, he was an active protester against Catholic propaganda, famous for his conversion of [[Kuči]] Vojvode [[Lale Drekalov]] from catholicism to orthodoxy.<ref name="наук)2001">{{cite book|author=Институт славяноведения и балканистики (Российская академия наук)|title=Османская Империя и страны Централ&ной, Восточной и Юго-Восточной Европы в 17 в.. 2(2001)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FSEsAQAAIAAJ|year=2001|publisher="Памятники исторической мысли"|page=218|quote=Новый митрополит Рувим Болевич после окончания Кандийской войны активно противодействовал католической пропаганде11. События в Черногории являлись отзвуком борьбы в Печской патриархии, очень обширной и потому ...}}</ref><ref>http://montenegrina.net/pages/pages1/istorija/plemena/drekalovici_porijeklo_vojvoda_drekale_m_miljanov.html</ref> He had notable influence on the [[Montenegrin tribes]], meeting with common folk and stopped [[krvna osveta|blood revenge]], and [[Anathema|cursing]] evil-doers.<ref name="Džomić2006">{{cite book|author=Velibor V. Džomić|title=Pravoslavlje u Crnoj Gori|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=leSQAAAAMAAJ|year=2006|publisher=Svetigora|quote=Митрополит Рувим (Бољевић) имао је велики утицај на племена. Стално је ишао по народу, мирио ...}}</ref> He had been a staunch supporter of the [[Republic of Venice]], and upon his death in January 1685, the Venetian Senate sent a letter to the [[List of Venetian governors of Kotor|Venetian governor of Kotor]], expressing their "sorrow for the Metropolitan of Cetinje, who always showed interest in our service".<ref name="StanojevićTadić1970">{{cite book|author1=Gligor Stanojević|author2=Jorjo Tadić|title=Jugoslovenske zemlje u mletačko-turskim ratovima XVI-XVIII vijeka|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ilUNAQAAIAAJ|year=1970|publisher=Istorijski institut|page=329|quote=Када ј« јаиуара 1685. улфо цетињоки митрополит Рувим,}}</ref> He was the most loyal friend of Venice of his time.<ref name="StanojevićTadić1970"/> He was buried in Gornje Brčele monastery.<ref>http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/planeta.300.html:553836-Cipur-Smiraj-23-mitropolita-kod-oltara</ref>
He was succeeded by Vasilije Veljekrajski, who is only mentioned by [[Nićifor Dučić]], without a lifespan or service period.<ref name="Ivanović2006"/>
A descendant of his, [[Arsenije Plamenac]], also served as Metropolitan (1781–1784).
==See also== *[[List of Metropolitans of Montenegro]]
==Annotations== *Name: His name is mostly spelled ''Rufim Boljević'' (Руфим Бољевић), while his given name can be spelled as ''Ruvim'' (Рувим) as well.
